cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper deals with state estimation of a battery pack using an electrochemical model and unscented Kalman filters. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) as well as embedded systems (cs.ET) since the battery pack is a critical component of many embedded systems. The use of reconfiguration also suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as unscented Kalman filters, which could place it under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the implementation of the state estimation scheme, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
